.TH AUXAGENT 1 "June 2026" "A/UX Workstation" "Local Commands"
.SH NAME
auxagent \- remote exec and file transfer agent (AAP over HTTP/1.0)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B auxagent
listens on port 8377 (boot-persistent via /etc/inittab) and speaks
AAP, a thin convention set over HTTP/1.0: every operation is a single
length-delimited request, connections are one-shot, and file
transfers carry a CRC-32.  It exists because telnet/ftp automation on
A/UX is unreliable (no framing, flush lag, leaky sessions).
.SH PROTOCOL
GET /ping returns the agent version.  POST /exec runs the body as a
shell command and returns merged output with X-Exit-Code.  GET and
PUT /file/<abspath> transfer files with X-Aap-Sum (CRC-32) integrity.
.SH CLIENT
Driven from the controlling Mac with auxctl: ping, exec, get, put,
and admin (which wraps /usr/local/auxadmin for workstation settings).
.SH CAVEAT
Commands run with stdin closed; programs that open the X display can
land the connection on fd 0 and break themselves - redirect stdin
from /dev/null (the xrdb merge in auxfont does exactly this).
.SH SEE ALSO
auxfont(1), DOCUMENT(7) in /DOCUMENT
